      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must directly correspond to the clinical decision metric at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary clinical hemolysis endpoint and is directly computed from CFD shear stress history. QoI relevance is fully established. Achieved Gradation 4."
